column5: Not 100% sure. If it's similar in size as S4_1_D_004, that lends confidence because 004 does not have brain pigment either.

Agree, Thunnus. They can have the lower jaw spots, usually very small. I think Nishikawa says that can be used to separate yellowfin and bigeye, but I did not find it reliable in PIPA when compared with genetic IDs.
Not Auxis, quite sure. Best ID is Thunnus. We can also report it as definitely either Katsuwonus or Thunnus, and still do backtracking.
Hm Auxis should be heavily pigmented along the ventral side of the tail even at earliest stages. If the pigment spots are super tiny, I'd be inclined to guess Thunnus. Tricky one.
